{"disposition":"accepted","experiment_id":"WM-001","findings":[{"id":"F001","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The terminal v1.16 attempt is scoped exactly: its accepted-binding rehearsal failed before child dispatch, formal-root creation, or outcome production because the standard-library launcher required a stale second-execution runtime filename instead of the authoritative content-addressed reproduction sidecar. No v1.16 performance value authorizes or informs v1.17."},{"id":"F002","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The standard-library launcher now reconstructs the development-audit package from terminal-bound execution and reproduction receipts, verifies every referenced runtime, invocation, stderr, and report payload by exact bytes and full SHA-256, enforces content-addressed reproduction names, and joins the reproduction sidecars to the second captured execution."},{"id":"F003","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The synthetic audit fixture was replaced by a production-writer composition path producing the exact 15 terminal-declared members. Acceptance and adversarial mutations exercise the real receipt writer and launcher consumer, including stale aliases, unsafe names, identity mismatches, cross-role substitutions, and semantic receipt mutations."},{"id":"F004","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The outer launcher now publishes one deterministic binding-keyed rehearsal claim and same-inode global marker before full authorization or child dispatch. The claim binds the canonical accepted binding, attempt, launcher, producer bootstrap, and fixed result-free command, and any existing claim or rehearsal state prevents a second child."},{"id":"F005","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Rehearsal publication is crash-aware and fail-closed across attempt creation, claim publication, child start, sidecars, terminal staging, canonical-terminal publication, cleanup, and outer completion. Recovery performs zero new dispatch, never rewrites or downgrades a terminal, completes only the same intact terminal inode, and otherwise publishes failed evidence or permanently rejects malformed state."},{"id":"F006","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"A separate rehearsal verifier strictly reopens the canonical five-file attempt, sole claim namespace, same-inode claim and completion markers, binding-equal stdout, empty stderr and outer receipt, formal-path absence, exact JSON types, source identities, link counts, descriptors, and namespace snapshots. Held custody rechecks all evidence before and after authority publication."},{"id":"F007","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Formal-launch representation v3 binds the authenticated canonical binding attempt and its outer completion plus the accepted rehearsal's exact claim, claim-marker, terminal, and outer-completion identities. Producer, verifier, independent auditor, and adjudicator all reopen the live canonical rehearsal, and producer-held descriptors are rechecked across global-marker publication."},{"id":"F008","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The outer launcher rescans formal readiness after accepted-rehearsal verification and immediately before child dispatch. It permits only the canonical non-aliased empty binding parent and rejects alternate confirmation, marker, audit, review, adjudication, staging, symlinked, non-directory, or nonempty current-version state."},{"id":"F009","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Historical seed custody was independently recomputed and corrected for the v1.10 development master 1156509260 and v1.14 formal master 671156171. A direct regression requires exact verifier/auditor tuples for every prior version; v1.17 has 10 fresh masters and 1360 fresh streams with zero internal or cross-domain collision against 160 prior masters and 21760 prior streams."},{"id":"F010","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The first unbound v1.17 preparation exposed a case-sensitive mismatch between the complete protocol verifier and the sealed formal-launch sentence. The verifier now matches the sealed uppercase sentence exactly, a direct regression executes the complete verifier, and the discarded environment created no lifecycle claim or outcome."},{"id":"F011","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The second unbound preparation exposed that the producer-side preformal mypy command omitted rehearsal.py while the independent auditor and runbook required it. The producer and auditor now share the exact 13-file type-check tuple, a direct tuple-equality regression prevents recurrence, and final preparation moves to fresh r3 environments without reusing either discarded preparation."},{"id":"F012","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Scientific continuity is exact: all 17 canonical scientific protocol blocks and the model, learning, planning, and runtime-lane kernels remain frozen from the corrected predecessor. The repair changes custody and authorization only, not algorithms, budgets, controls, metrics, thresholds, gates, or exclusions."},{"id":"F013","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Representation continuity is explicit: protocol representation v9, formal-binding v10, raw-result v9, and preformal/prebinding representations v2 remain unchanged. Only formal-launch advances to v3 because it adds the accepted-rehearsal authorization identities."},{"id":"F014","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The plan and runbook freeze fresh r3 QA/runtime environments, wheel and lock custody, staged implementation-manifest review binding, repeated lifecycle-path absence checks, static gates, development, audit, closure, preformal, binding, preflight, rehearsal, formal launch, semantic review, and adjudication order. The formal binding root is created only after independently accepted rehearsal evidence."},{"id":"F015","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"Prospective coverage is deliberately compositional: decisive real writer, receipt consumer, rehearsal transaction, crash recovery, formal-launch custody, verifier, auditor, and adjudicator boundaries are exercised without claiming that one heavyweight fixture duplicates the complete production lifecycle before the prospective run."},{"id":"F016","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"The assurance boundary remains explicit and is not external attestation or same-principal tamper resistance: repository, environment, path, filesystem, base-interpreter, kernel, and cooperative-lock integrity remain trusted."}],"implementation_files":[{"bytes":1685,"path":"Makefile","sha256":"b21f5399f884826642c7711dc69c0ae192d602f79613614eeb342fb5cb519a64"},{"bytes":148,"path":"bench/__init__.py","sha256":"6c7b9de75c247ced5f62064f9786cf6e2f14d958bd1be6eb65c6ed69680b6942"},{"bytes":561,"path":"bench/epistemic/__init__.py","sha256":"bb77dc8aba3b32b6bc2df16a5abd9fc24b0ece2a389e814c3337a0f637a5467e"},{"bytes":44718,"path":"bench/epistemic/lifecycle.py","sha256":"3d30d947ca830a0c307f2e7f40d31bc4bef51d497f2e96d68f000fa864e3ed25"},{"bytes":30661,"path":"bench/epistemic/maturity.py","sha256":"2a81abe60f12285f66f2bcd351589de28851412f1d9df7f2003843a845a2510e"},{"bytes":13611,"path":"bench/epistemic/problem.py","sha256":"c66ae13d3e833ffd1be1562a89e0e9035d6197b95723179b930c1ca2a1059c66"},{"bytes":1097,"path":"bench/epistemic/run_maturity.py","sha256":"86ae2c3175262f559a274827c96c30212fbdb9250e3a4614f92c861b7498feb7"},{"bytes":20656,"path":"bench/epistemic/runtime_lane.py","sha256":"d8f0c7a85be786c3a813ee1f169abcbc2791a642e46fba5978f7a1140cc50387"},{"bytes":278,"path":"bench/world_model_lifecycle/SEALED_PROTOCOL.sha256","sha256":"88fa5c59f6217ed925888b338f8f601e37e2ae6d6ae47ba1cbda8f50f08dfebb"},{"bytes":75,"path":"bench/world_model_lifecycle/__init__.py","sha256":"0390d290ffee36c3e2a696938bab498fddba3991f